"489","<p style=margin-bottom:13.9pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;line-height:13.8pt;>In planning and performing our audits of the financial"
"490","statements of Dreyfus Equity Income Fund and Dreyfus Emerging Markets Debt"
"491","Local Currency Fund, each a series of Dreyfus/Laurel Funds Trust (collectively,"
"492","the &#8220;Funds&#8221;) as of and for the year ended May 31, 2013, in accordance with the"
"493","standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we"
"494","considered the Funds&#8217; internal control over financial reporting, including"
"495","controls over safeguarding securities, as a basis for designing our auditing"
"496","procedures for the purpose of expressing our opinion on the financial"
"497","statements and to comply with the requirements of Form N-SAR, but not for the"
"498","purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the Funds&#8217; internal"
"499","control over financial reporting. Accordingly, we express no such opinion. </font></p>"
"500","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;>Management of the Funds is responsible for"
"501","establishing and maintaining effective internal control over financial"
"502","reporting. In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates and judgments by"
"503","management are required to assess the expected benefits and related costs of"
"504","controls.&#160; A fund&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting is a process"
"505","designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial"
"506","reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in"
"507","accordance with generally accepted accounting principles (GAAP). A fund's"
"508","internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and"
"509","procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable"
"510","detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the"
"511","assets of the fund; (2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are"
"512","recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in"
"513","accordance with GAAP, and that receipts and expenditures of the fund are being"
"514","made only in accordance with authorizations of management and directors/trustees"
"515","of the fund; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or"
"516","timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition of a fund's"
"517","assets that could have a material effect on the financial statements.</font></p>"
"518","<p style=margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;line-height:13.8pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"519","<p style=margin-bottom:13.9pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;line-height:13.8pt;>Because of its inherent limitations, internal"
"520","control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also,"
"521","projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject to"
"522","the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions,"
"523","or that the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may"
"524","deteriorate. </font></p>"
